# Remotion component authoring

Before writing or changing Remotion code in this repo, read:

1. `skills/remotion/docs/INDEX.md` — mirrored official docs (same MDX as remotion.dev)
2. `skills/remotion/SKILL.md` — project conventions
3. `skills/remotion/rules/video-layout.md` — layout slots, no overlap

Refresh docs: `pnpm docs:remotion`

## Non-negotiables (from official Remotion docs)

- Animate with `useCurrentFrame()` + `interpolate()` / `spring()` — **never** CSS transitions or Tailwind animation classes
- **`AbsoluteFill`** — full-frame scenes and backgrounds only, **not** wrappers around list items
- **Inline wrappers** — use `MotionWrapper` (`skills/remotion/.../lib/motion-wrapper.tsx`) for enter/exit on children in flex/grid
- **Stagger** — `<Sequence from={…} layout="none">` via `StaggerChildren`; do not stack multiple `AbsoluteFill` siblings
- **Layout** — flex column + `gap` for readable content; one slot per element (`video-layout.md`)
- **Typewriter** — string slicing only; optional blinking cursor (`skills/remotion/rules/text-animations.md`)

## RemotionUI paths

- Registry source: `apps/web/registry/bases/default/`
- Manifest: `apps/web/registry.json` (add `registryDependencies` for new libs)
- Previews: `apps/web/components/previews/` + `<RemotionPreview>` in `content/docs/`
- After changes: `pnpm registry:build` then `pnpm qa:browser`

## Version note

This project uses `remotion@^4.0.473`. Use `premountFor` on full-frame `<Sequence>` only — not with `layout="none"` (see `Sequence.d.ts`).
